01:38.566 --> 01:40.132
What the hell?

01:40.134 --> 01:41.567
Her hair, her dress --

01:41.569 --> 01:43.302
It's like she's ready
for a '70s costume party.

01:43.304 --> 01:45.104
Could be
an extra in a movie.

01:45.106 --> 01:48.440
Maybe they're finally remaking
"saturday night fever."

01:48.442 --> 01:51.076
Did i ever tell you
that was my first r-rated movie?

01:51.078 --> 01:53.412
It's come up. I'm gonna
need henry on this one.

01:53.414 --> 01:56.648
They used to say my hair
and travolta's was identical --

01:56.650 --> 01:59.318
Thick, jet-black,
the perfect sheen.

01:59.320 --> 02:00.719
Tell you
about this, too?

02:00.721 --> 02:02.821
It has come up.

02:02.823 --> 02:03.822
Sorry.

02:03.824 --> 02:06.125
[ mid-tempo music playing ]

02:08.295 --> 02:09.628
[ box thuds ]

02:10.798 --> 02:13.232
Oh, goodness gracious, abraham,
what's that?

02:13.234 --> 02:17.569
That, sir, is the aroma of,
uh, wet cardboard and mold.

02:17.571 --> 02:20.272
It was so cold last night, one
of the pipes burst in the attic.

02:20.274 --> 02:23.275
Fortunately, this is
the only box that got soaked.

02:23.277 --> 02:25.077
Not your
baseball cards, i hope.

02:25.079 --> 02:27.746
No, those i have in
a safety-deposit box.

02:27.748 --> 02:29.314
This is just
some old junk.

02:29.316 --> 02:33.318
Baby abraham's
bronzed booties.

02:33.320 --> 02:34.987
Yeah. Stopped fitting
a long time ago.

02:34.989 --> 02:36.421
[ chuckles ]

02:36.423 --> 02:38.357
It's just sentimental
garbage, you know,

02:38.359 --> 02:39.591
Without any real value.

02:39.593 --> 02:41.193
Well, it's
part of your past.

02:41.195 --> 02:44.163
Yeah, well, what i want to keep,
i keep up here.

02:44.165 --> 02:46.665
If not, i just forget it,
make room for the new.

02:46.667 --> 02:48.767
The other stuff
belongs in a landfill.

02:53.807 --> 02:55.641
Oh, uh...

02:55.643 --> 02:57.376
Mom's cookbook.

02:57.378 --> 03:00.045
I, uh,
didn't see that.

03:00.047 --> 03:01.346
Um...I'm sorry.

03:01.348 --> 03:03.215
That was not junk.

03:05.486 --> 03:07.519
Perhaps you're right,
abraham.

03:07.521 --> 03:09.021
It's a new day.

03:09.023 --> 03:10.556
There are new memories
to be made.

03:10.558 --> 03:12.357
I'm off.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.359
¶ let me get to know you ¶

03:14.361 --> 03:17.362
Henry:<i> We are told</i>
<i>that those who ignore the past</i>

03:17.364 --> 03:19.064
<i>Are doomed to repeat it,</i>

03:19.066 --> 03:21.033
<i>While those</i>
<i>who dwell in the past</i>

03:21.035 --> 03:23.402
<i>Would love nothing more</i>
<i>than to repeat it</i>

03:23.404 --> 03:25.704
<i>Over and over again.</i>

03:25.706 --> 03:30.709
<i>But memories, like photographs,</i>
<i>have a way of fading with time.</i>

03:30.711 --> 03:33.312
Well, based on
the amount of blood,

03:33.314 --> 03:36.481
We figure she bled out from
her neck wound, made by this.

03:36.483 --> 03:37.883
Lucas:
Oh, i love fondue!

03:37.885 --> 03:40.319
You can go, like, savory
with cheese

03:40.321 --> 03:42.154
Or sweet with chocolate,

03:42.156 --> 03:44.056
But the best part --
it's social. [ chuckles ]

03:44.058 --> 03:47.092
And, therefore, a petri dish
for communicable diseases.

03:47.094 --> 03:49.561
I'll get this tested.
Yum.

03:49.563 --> 03:50.929
Mike: So, doc,
bruises on her wrists

03:50.931 --> 03:52.397
Suggest she might have
been held down.

03:52.399 --> 03:53.398
That's amazing.

03:53.400 --> 03:54.666
What's amazing?

03:54.668 --> 03:56.368
Her hair.

03:56.370 --> 03:57.502
It smells of...

03:57.504 --> 03:58.403
Garbage?

03:58.405 --> 04:00.239
...Chlorofluorocarbons,

04:00.241 --> 04:03.408
Used in aerosol products
like hair spray in the '70s,

04:03.410 --> 04:04.610
Before it was banned.

04:04.612 --> 04:06.245
I wonder...

04:06.247 --> 04:08.614
Yeah, we were thinking
the vintage outfit she's wearing

04:08.616 --> 04:10.916
Might point to
an actor in costume.

04:10.918 --> 04:13.919
Well, no costume
is<i> this</i> exact, no.

04:13.921 --> 04:17.289
Our victim's nail polish
contains phthalate ester,

04:17.291 --> 04:18.790
A plasticizer,

04:18.792 --> 04:21.627
Discontinued due to
its carcinogenic properties.

04:21.629 --> 04:23.729
The anachronisms
don't stop there.

04:23.731 --> 04:27.065
This wrap is
a von furstenberg original.

04:27.067 --> 04:29.034
Every item is vintage.

04:29.036 --> 04:31.603
What are we talking about here,
doc -- a time traveler?

04:31.605 --> 04:33.639
Or a victim
who was obsessed with the past,

04:33.641 --> 04:35.774
And speaking
of obsessions,

04:35.776 --> 04:37.943
Due to the voyeuristic nature
of these photographs,

04:37.945 --> 04:41.580
I'd wager that our victim was
the object of someone's fantasy.

04:41.582 --> 04:44.650
Which turned into
a nightmare.

04:53.093 --> 04:55.961
Jo: The victim bled out
when her carotid was cut.

04:55.963 --> 04:58.330
And the fondue skewer
we recovered matches the wound.

04:58.332 --> 05:00.265
Just when you think
you've heard it all.

05:00.267 --> 05:01.633
Have we run her
past vice?

05:01.635 --> 05:03.802
Yeah, but we're not sure
she's a prostitute.

05:03.804 --> 05:05.404
Based on her wardrobe,

05:05.406 --> 05:07.406
Henry thinks she was part of
some weird '70s fantasy.

05:07.408 --> 05:09.408
Well, who knew we had
anna wintour downstairs

05:09.410 --> 05:10.776
Doing our autopsies?

05:10.778 --> 05:12.144
Missing persons
came back with reports

05:12.146 --> 05:13.679
Matching our jane doe's
description.

05:13.681 --> 05:15.747
We got a match --
sarah clancy,

05:15.749 --> 05:18.750
Junior at n.Y.U., reported
missing by her roommate.

05:18.752 --> 05:21.253
It's hard to believe
it's the same girl.

05:21.255 --> 05:22.854
Jo, talk to
the roommate.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.523
Hanson, go back
to the landfill.

05:24.525 --> 05:26.992
See if you can
trace back from the dump site

05:26.994 --> 05:29.428
To find out where
our victim was murdered.

05:31.298 --> 05:33.732
See what happens
when you pick up the phone?

05:37.971 --> 05:39.771
Jennifer:
We met our first day.

05:39.773 --> 05:42.207
We were both
from small towns,

05:42.209 --> 05:44.343
In the city
for the first time.

05:44.345 --> 05:47.946
The fact that we ended up
as roommates, it was perfect...

05:47.948 --> 05:49.448
[ laughs ]

05:49.450 --> 05:53.018
...Like sarah and i had been
friends our whole lives.

05:53.020 --> 05:55.987
Jo: Had sarah been dealing
with any personal issues?

05:55.989 --> 05:58.790
New boyfriend,
bad breakup maybe?

05:58.792 --> 06:00.459
I don't know.

06:00.461 --> 06:03.428
I thought you were
best friends.

06:03.964 --> 06:08.367
We<i> were</i> v-very close,
and then we weren't.

06:08.369 --> 06:11.903
Henry: Sarah may have arrived
in new york a small-town girl,

06:11.905 --> 06:13.805
But she was changing,
wasn't she?

06:13.807 --> 06:17.542
Rather a sophisticated
wardrobe.

06:17.544 --> 06:20.912
Not exactly
contemporary couture, is it?

06:20.914 --> 06:23.548
Jennifer,
you can talk to us.

06:23.550 --> 06:26.418
We just want to find
the person who did this.

06:26.420 --> 06:28.720
She had changed.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.622
[ thunder rumbling ]

06:31.658 --> 06:33.592
And not just the way
that she looked.

06:33.594 --> 06:36.228
Do you have any idea
who or what

06:36.230 --> 06:38.497
Would be responsible
for this transformation?

06:39.833 --> 06:42.033
She had become
so secretive.

06:42.035 --> 06:45.270
Dropped all of her classes,
except for one.

06:45.272 --> 06:48.673
It was like
she was obsessed with it.

06:49.777 --> 06:51.209
Which class?

06:51.211 --> 06:53.945
Professor: What urge
creates these fantasies?

06:53.947 --> 06:56.915
Is it control,

06:56.917 --> 07:00.051
Power, transformation?

07:00.053 --> 07:04.423
If our fantasies are fed
by our deepest desires...
Is it just me,
or has college changed?

07:04.425 --> 07:07.926
...Then understanding them
can teach us who we truly are...
Since freud, psychology has
become obsessed with sexuality.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.461
...And what we wish
to become.

07:09.463 --> 07:11.296
Lights.
I've always
found it rather...

07:14.735 --> 07:16.034
...Stimulating.

07:21.308 --> 07:25.444
We all have someone or something
we fantasize about.

07:25.446 --> 07:29.247
The question is, what
could we learn about ourselves

07:29.249 --> 07:31.049
If we gave in
to that desire?

07:31.051 --> 07:34.085
That's all i have for today.
Thank you.

07:34.087 --> 07:36.288
[ indistinct chatter ]

07:40.394 --> 07:42.227
Iona.

07:42.229 --> 07:45.063
Oh, that's professor dawes
in the classroom.

07:45.065 --> 07:46.431
You can call me molly.

07:46.433 --> 07:48.500
Well, it's a pleasure
to see you again, molly.

07:48.502 --> 07:49.734
You may call me henry.

07:51.338 --> 07:53.104
You are
full of surprises.

07:53.106 --> 07:55.240
Therapist, dominatrix,

07:55.242 --> 07:56.842
Professor?

07:56.844 --> 07:59.077
Well, i do have a phd
in psychology from yale,

07:59.079 --> 08:00.779
So the head of the department
calls me in

08:00.781 --> 08:02.414
Any time there's
subject matter

08:02.416 --> 08:04.182
Her staff isn't
as well-versed in.

08:04.184 --> 08:05.984
Such as sexual fantasy.

08:05.986 --> 08:09.788
Which is exactly what we've
come here to discuss.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.823
Professionally, of course.

08:11.825 --> 08:13.658
Molly:
I can't believe she's dead.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.260
Jo:
Did you know sarah well?

08:15.262 --> 08:17.095
We had a lot in common.

08:17.097 --> 08:20.465
She and i both had
very sheltered childhoods.

08:20.467 --> 08:22.968
She was different
from the rest of my students.

08:22.970 --> 08:24.336
She was very mature.

08:24.338 --> 08:26.605
Did she talk a lot
about her personal life?

08:26.607 --> 08:28.707
We're trying
to find out...

08:28.709 --> 08:30.442
Who took these.

08:32.379 --> 08:35.480
She did come to office hours
a few weeks ago --

08:35.482 --> 08:36.548
Not about class.

08:36.550 --> 08:38.049
She told me

08:38.051 --> 08:41.219
That she was involved in
a role-playing relationship

08:41.221 --> 08:43.455
And she knew
it wasn't normal, per se.

08:43.457 --> 08:45.957
Did she know
about your...

08:45.959 --> 08:48.460
Secondary occupation?

08:48.462 --> 08:51.897
That i'm
a domination therapist?

08:51.899 --> 08:53.465
That's why
i felt obliged

08:53.467 --> 08:56.167
To ask her if she enjoyed it
and if she felt safe,

08:56.169 --> 08:57.969
And she said yes.

08:57.971 --> 08:59.271
But...

09:00.307 --> 09:03.708
...If she was wrong
and then i didn't...

09:03.710 --> 09:05.377
It's not your fault.

09:07.548 --> 09:09.681
Perhaps there's a way
i can help.

09:09.683 --> 09:11.850
I mean, if there's anything
that you can tell me about
the crime scene, then --

09:11.852 --> 09:13.318
Thank you, professor,

09:13.320 --> 09:14.719
But we have
new york city's finest on it.

09:17.391 --> 09:19.191
Thank you.

09:19.192 --> 09:20.992
Lucas: You sure they only
gave us one hazmat suit?

09:20.994 --> 09:24.062
Mike: What?
Oh, uh, cutbacks, i guess.

09:24.064 --> 09:27.999
Wow, great article on
jimmy caan's walk-in humidor.

09:28.001 --> 09:29.734
I think
i found something --

09:29.736 --> 09:32.737
A possible location
for the crime scene.

09:32.739 --> 09:34.406
[ sighs ]
i did a reagent search

09:34.408 --> 09:37.542
On all the debris near where
the victim's body was found

09:37.544 --> 09:40.312
And picked up traces of blood
on this junk mail.

09:41.915 --> 09:45.183
All from the same
apartment building.

09:45.185 --> 09:46.918
Thinking that's
where she was killed

09:46.920 --> 09:48.920
And then dumped the body here
with the rest of the garbage?

09:48.922 --> 09:50.789
We got an address.
Blow it up?

09:50.791 --> 09:51.890
You need a shower.

09:51.892 --> 09:53.191
[ chuckles ]
i'm calling joe.

09:53.193 --> 09:54.593
I'm gonna need
my own badge soon.

09:54.595 --> 09:55.894
Mike:
Yeah, aim high, lucas.

09:55.896 --> 09:57.562
Come on,
an honorary badge, something.

09:57.564 --> 10:00.065
Man:
Sarah was a real good tenant.

10:00.067 --> 10:02.634
Huh, yeah,
always paid on time, quiet.

10:02.636 --> 10:04.603
Was there a boyfriend,
an older gentleman perhaps?

10:04.605 --> 10:06.137
No.

10:06.139 --> 10:07.939
Do you have
surveillance?

10:07.941 --> 10:10.108
This is
an older building.

10:10.110 --> 10:12.210
Well, when it was built,
it was state-of-the-art.

10:12.212 --> 10:13.211
You should've seen it.

10:13.213 --> 10:15.080
It was just like...

10:15.082 --> 10:17.349
What the hell?

10:19.319 --> 10:21.920
Uh...

10:21.922 --> 10:22.921
Thank you.

10:22.923 --> 10:24.122
[ closet door opens ]

10:25.626 --> 10:29.761
There is not one article
of clothing in this closet.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.329
[ closet door closes ]

10:31.331 --> 10:33.298
Ah.

10:33.300 --> 10:36.635
A technics sl-220 --
40 years old.

10:36.637 --> 10:38.903
Like it just
came out of the box.

10:38.905 --> 10:40.739
We had
the exact same one.

10:42.242 --> 10:43.408
In the shop.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.479
Check out
these magazines.

10:47.481 --> 10:51.383
They're all from the same year
and the same month.

10:57.157 --> 10:59.991
This fondue set
is original, too.

10:59.993 --> 11:04.195
Every item in this place
has been carefully chosen

11:04.197 --> 11:07.999
To create a perfect simulacrum
of the late 1970s.

11:08.001 --> 11:11.703
Everything is in accord
with that design.

11:11.705 --> 11:14.372
Everything
except for this.

11:14.374 --> 11:15.774
The little rug?

11:18.445 --> 11:20.512
It's a macramé
wall hanging --

11:20.514 --> 11:22.681
Very popular at the time

11:22.683 --> 11:25.183
And never ever
placed on the floor.

11:25.185 --> 11:26.751
No,
that would be insane.

11:30.524 --> 11:32.390
I believe we've found
our crime scene.

11:32.392 --> 11:34.159
But if the victim
bled out slowly,

11:34.161 --> 11:36.127
Why would the blood
be concentrated here?

11:36.129 --> 11:37.629
Why didn't she get up,
go for help?

11:37.631 --> 11:39.197
You think
she was knocked out?

11:39.199 --> 11:42.467
Perhaps the killer held her down
and watched her die.

11:45.405 --> 11:47.138
Hey.

11:47.140 --> 11:48.640
Look at this.

11:50.544 --> 11:52.544
Another polaroid.

11:52.546 --> 11:54.779
This one
looks different.

11:56.383 --> 11:58.349
Polaroids fade.

11:58.351 --> 12:02.187
And judging by
the deterioration of this image,

12:02.189 --> 12:05.457
I'd say this one
was actually taken in the '70s.

12:09.896 --> 12:12.263
This isn't
the same girl,

12:12.265 --> 12:14.165
But they're both wearing
the same dress.

12:14.167 --> 12:16.034
So, who is this woman?

12:16.036 --> 12:19.170
The woman sarah
was supposed to be.

12:24.277 --> 12:25.410
The apartment was a perfect
replica of a 1970s home,

12:25.412 --> 12:27.045
Exact in every detail.

12:27.047 --> 12:29.013
What do you mean,
like, disco,

12:29.015 --> 12:31.015
Uh, polyester,
nixon?

12:31.017 --> 12:34.085
Not the 20th century's
finest hour, but...

12:34.087 --> 12:35.520
[ sighs ]

12:35.522 --> 12:38.256
Iona -- molly --
believes that it was part of

12:38.258 --> 12:40.592
Some sort of
role-playing fantasy.

12:40.594 --> 12:42.026
Iona.

12:42.028 --> 12:44.596
As in
your dominatrix gal pal?

12:44.598 --> 12:46.264
Eh, professor.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.800
She teaches
a psychology class at n.Y.U.

12:48.802 --> 12:50.568
Oh, now i get it.

12:50.570 --> 12:52.103
New scarf.

12:52.105 --> 12:54.706
You're dressed
to impress, henry.

12:54.708 --> 12:56.107
Look, i'll grant you

12:56.109 --> 12:58.543
That, uh, molly
is a fascinating woman,

12:58.545 --> 13:01.112
But my interest in her
is strictly professional.

13:01.114 --> 13:03.481
I hear
she's very strict.

13:03.483 --> 13:04.916
[ chuckles ]

13:04.918 --> 13:06.384
No, i know. I know.
I get it. I get it.

13:06.386 --> 13:08.219
You're scared.
Okay, so, it's been a long time

13:08.221 --> 13:09.954
And you're
out of practice.

13:09.956 --> 13:11.256
I'm not a monk.

13:11.258 --> 13:13.625
I've had relations.

13:13.627 --> 13:15.126
No, no, i know.

13:15.128 --> 13:16.728
You've had sex, yeah, with
countless beautiful women.

13:16.730 --> 13:19.297
Oh, you've got that immortal
charm going for you, i know,

13:19.299 --> 13:21.299
But none of them
have ever gone anywhere, henry.

13:21.301 --> 13:22.901
I mean,
do you even remember

13:22.903 --> 13:26.571
Going out on a date with
someone you actually cared for?

13:26.573 --> 13:29.073
<i>[ jazz music playing ]</i>

13:31.311 --> 13:34.112
Abigail dear, you ready?

13:34.114 --> 13:37.916
Reservations at la camilia
are not easy to come by.

13:37.918 --> 13:40.485
Dino will give
our table away.

13:40.487 --> 13:43.421
Abigail: Are you sure
we shouldn't stay in?

13:43.423 --> 13:45.590
[ sighs ]

13:45.592 --> 13:47.458
It's our anniversary.

13:47.460 --> 13:49.928
Oh, darling henry,
i don't know.

13:49.930 --> 13:51.796
Really, what will
people think?

13:51.798 --> 13:54.766
An older woman
with her young escort.

13:54.768 --> 13:57.168
[ sighs ]
we're a
distinguished couple

13:57.170 --> 13:59.370
Out for
a sophisticated dinner

13:59.372 --> 14:01.773
And a spot
of unsophisticated dancing,

14:01.775 --> 14:03.208
Courtesy of
my two left feet.

14:03.210 --> 14:06.711
[ chuckles ] but you're
a marvelous dancer.

14:06.713 --> 14:08.913
Everyone will stare at us.

14:09.983 --> 14:13.451
We've braved
a war together,

14:13.453 --> 14:15.486
Raised a child together.

14:15.488 --> 14:18.890
I'm sure we can survive a night
out in new york together.
[ chuckles ]

14:18.892 --> 14:20.391
Come on. It'll be fun.

14:20.393 --> 14:22.560
You're right.

14:22.562 --> 14:25.196
Let's have fun.

14:25.198 --> 14:27.932
[ siren wailing in distance ]

14:29.035 --> 14:30.301
I had a thought.

14:30.303 --> 14:32.370
New scarf?
Yes.

14:32.372 --> 14:34.138
Now, i don't usually
have a say

14:34.140 --> 14:36.040
In how we manage
an investigation,

14:36.042 --> 14:38.376
But i had a thought.
You mentioned
this thought.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.211
What if we were to
involve professor dawes

14:40.213 --> 14:41.713
As a psychological profiler

14:41.715 --> 14:43.414
With an eye toward
sexual fantasies?

14:43.416 --> 14:44.849
Thank you, henry,

14:44.851 --> 14:47.218
But i think we have it covered
without molly.

14:47.220 --> 14:50.989
Jo!
We got something.

14:53.727 --> 14:55.526
Forensics pulled video
from sarah's laptop.

14:55.528 --> 14:57.328
[ keyboard clacks ]

14:57.330 --> 15:00.732
<i>You must be exhausted, dear.</i>
<i>Take off your jacket.</i>

15:00.734 --> 15:04.769
<i>Subway construction was just</i>
<i>awful today at 59th and lex.</i>

15:04.771 --> 15:07.605
<i>I had to walk two blocks</i>
<i>to get home.</i>

15:07.607 --> 15:09.574
<i>Poor baby.</i>

15:09.576 --> 15:11.175
<i>You look tense.</i>

15:12.746 --> 15:15.013
<i>I know just the thing</i>
<i>to calm you down.</i>

15:15.015 --> 15:16.147
[<i> door opens</i> ]
[<i> gasps</i> ]

15:16.149 --> 15:19.384
<i>Sorry.</i> [<i> sighs</i> ]
[<i> door closes</i> ]

15:19.386 --> 15:21.219
<i>My roommate's home.</i>

15:21.221 --> 15:22.754
<i>I'm not much of an actress,</i>

15:22.756 --> 15:25.356
<i>But i'm interested</i>
<i>in your offer.</i>

15:25.358 --> 15:28.459
<i>I hope</i>
<i>we can play together.</i>

15:28.461 --> 15:29.894
Almost like
she's auditioning.

15:29.896 --> 15:32.397
What kind of killer
puts out a casting call?

15:32.399 --> 15:36.701
Perhaps the insights
of an expert would be helpful.

15:38.538 --> 15:41.706
Okay, henry, let's go
talk to your girlfriend.

15:45.946 --> 15:48.112
Oh, please, doctor,
do go on.

15:48.114 --> 15:51.716
Well, most fantasies
are flights of fancy.

15:51.718 --> 15:53.551
They're scenarios

15:53.553 --> 15:55.787
That the participants can't
live out in their normal lives.

15:55.789 --> 15:57.322
But this one
couldn't be more ordinary.

15:57.324 --> 15:58.990
Exactly, so...

15:58.992 --> 16:02.794
The man who concocted it,
his fantasy is about control.

16:02.796 --> 16:06.397
[ sighs ] he dresses her,
puts her in this apartment...

16:07.968 --> 16:10.768
...And tells her
what to say.

16:10.770 --> 16:14.072
Some men seek that out,
to dominate a woman.

16:14.074 --> 16:16.507
Others look
to be dominated.

16:16.509 --> 16:17.909
At its simplest,

16:17.911 --> 16:20.211
It's really just about
who wants to be on top.

16:21.348 --> 16:23.281
New scarf?

16:23.283 --> 16:24.415
New fragrance?

16:24.417 --> 16:26.017
Professor dawes?

16:26.019 --> 16:27.318
Hmm?

16:27.320 --> 16:28.753
You see anything else
in the video?

16:28.755 --> 16:31.122
This fantasy
isn't about domination,

16:31.124 --> 16:33.024
It's about re-creation.

16:33.026 --> 16:35.860
A memory.

16:35.862 --> 16:38.196
A moment from his past.

16:38.198 --> 16:41.332
The last time he was happy,
in love, something,

16:41.334 --> 16:44.035
But you're looking for a man
in his mid 60s,

16:44.037 --> 16:47.338
Maybe, um, a doctor,
a scientist,

16:47.340 --> 16:49.674
But somebody
who employs exacting control

16:49.676 --> 16:52.510
In their work
and their life.

16:52.512 --> 16:54.779
[<i> rewinding</i> ]

16:55.982 --> 16:59.884
<i>Subway construction was just</i>
<i>awful today at 59th and lex.</i>

16:59.886 --> 17:03.154
<i>I had to walk two blocks</i>
<i>to get home.</i>

17:03.156 --> 17:06.124
If this fantasy is about
a moment from our killer's past,

17:06.126 --> 17:08.226
Then all of these details
are meaningful.

17:08.228 --> 17:09.660
Wait.

17:09.662 --> 17:12.230
There was a massive
subway construction

17:12.232 --> 17:15.700
At 59th and lexington
in 1979,

17:15.702 --> 17:17.068
Blocks away
from the crime scene,

17:17.070 --> 17:18.302
Which begs the question...

17:18.304 --> 17:20.438
Who rented that apartment
in 1979?

17:23.543 --> 17:27.045
Can you confirm
that you leased an apartment

17:27.047 --> 17:31.816
At, um, 112 east 61st street
in 1979?

17:31.818 --> 17:33.584
I don't remember.

17:33.586 --> 17:37.088
The lease has you listed
as tenant from 1978 to 1982.

17:37.090 --> 17:39.891
That's a long time ago,
but it sounds right.

17:39.893 --> 17:41.426
Um...

17:41.428 --> 17:43.027
That is not
for sightseeing.

17:43.029 --> 17:46.164
So, what is this about?

17:46.166 --> 17:49.700
A woman was murdered
in your old apartment.

17:49.702 --> 17:51.302
Her name
was sarah clancy.

17:53.106 --> 17:54.605
Maybe you remember
seeing her somewhere?

17:54.607 --> 17:55.606
Mnh-mnh.

17:55.608 --> 17:58.643
How about this woman?

18:03.716 --> 18:06.417
Thank you for your time,
mr. Neville.

18:06.419 --> 18:08.252
Hey, wait. No, don't.

18:08.254 --> 18:09.353
Stop.

18:09.355 --> 18:10.521
You're gonna
destroy that.

18:10.523 --> 18:12.256
It's very delicate.

18:12.258 --> 18:14.092
Please.

18:15.228 --> 18:17.095
Give me the picture.

18:17.097 --> 18:19.230
Who was she?

18:19.232 --> 18:23.301
My wife...Catelyn.

18:23.303 --> 18:25.069
When did she die?

18:25.071 --> 18:27.472
1981, breast cancer.

18:27.474 --> 18:28.906
The picture
you just destroyed

18:28.908 --> 18:32.110
I took a few weeks
before she was diagnosed.

18:35.782 --> 18:38.282
[ sighs ]

18:38.284 --> 18:40.685
Where were you
two nights ago, mr. Neville?

18:41.955 --> 18:43.421
I was there.

18:43.423 --> 18:45.523
With sarah
in the apartment?

18:46.459 --> 18:47.792
[ sighs ]

18:47.794 --> 18:49.861
What happened to sarah,
mr. Neville?

18:51.631 --> 18:52.997
I think i killed her.

18:58.938 --> 19:00.738
Jo:<i> Can you tell us</i>
<i>how a man like you</i>

19:00.740 --> 19:03.141
<i>Came to meet a 20-year-old</i>
<i>undergraduate student --</i>

19:03.143 --> 19:05.243
Sarah clancy?

19:05.245 --> 19:08.479
I was downtown for a building
inspection, and i saw her.

19:08.481 --> 19:10.815
<i>At first,</i>
<i>i could've sworn it was --</i>

19:10.817 --> 19:12.049
Your wife?

19:13.353 --> 19:14.952
So much alike,

19:14.954 --> 19:16.754
The pieces fell into place
as soon as i saw her.

19:16.756 --> 19:19.423
I could rent the apartment,
remodel.

19:19.425 --> 19:22.827
I wanted it
to be as real as possible.

19:22.829 --> 19:24.662
Okay, what'd you
make sarah do,

19:24.664 --> 19:26.330
Other than impersonate
your dead wife?

19:26.332 --> 19:28.299
I didn't<i> make</i> her
do anything.

19:28.301 --> 19:30.001
I hired her,
and she was compensated.

19:30.003 --> 19:32.336
Oh, i'm sure it was all
very romantic

19:32.338 --> 19:33.838
Till she ended up dead.

19:33.840 --> 19:36.841
Okay, night of the murder --
tell us what happened.

19:36.843 --> 19:39.877
The same thing as always --
i came home to the apartment.

19:39.879 --> 19:42.113
It wasn't some random night
he was re-creating.

19:42.115 --> 19:43.514
<i>She asked about work,</i>
<i>handed me a drink...</i>
It was<i> the</i> night.

19:43.516 --> 19:44.615
<i>...And then lead me</i>
<i>to the living room.</i>

19:44.617 --> 19:46.384
The best moment
in his life.

19:46.386 --> 19:48.352
And what did sarah do?

19:48.354 --> 19:50.721
She tells me she's just
found out she's pregnant...

19:50.723 --> 19:52.323
I'm pregnant.

19:52.325 --> 19:55.359
...Just the way
my late wife told me.

19:55.361 --> 19:57.828
And in my excitement,
i take her picture

19:57.830 --> 19:59.297
Because i want
to remember that moment

19:59.299 --> 20:01.065
For the rest of my life.
[ camera shutter clicks ]

20:01.067 --> 20:03.367
But each time...

20:03.369 --> 20:04.969
The moment
seemed to slip

20:04.971 --> 20:07.305
Farther and farther
into the past.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.807
...It felt
fainter somehow.

20:09.809 --> 20:11.075
Is that why
you killed her?

20:11.077 --> 20:13.211
The fantasy
wasn't realistic enough?

20:13.213 --> 20:16.214
She had
her cellphone, and...

20:16.216 --> 20:19.383
I forbade any items
from sarah's regular life,

20:19.385 --> 20:21.552
And that threw me off.
Made you angry.

20:21.554 --> 20:23.421
She ruined your fantasy.

20:23.423 --> 20:24.655
So, you stabbed her,
didn't you?

20:24.657 --> 20:26.557
I think so. Yes.

20:27.994 --> 20:29.560
With what?

20:29.562 --> 20:32.930
The skewer
from the fondue set.

20:32.932 --> 20:35.299
Show us
how you did it.

20:37.537 --> 20:40.238
In the neck once...

20:40.240 --> 20:42.406
<i>Like that.</i>

20:42.408 --> 20:44.875
[ telephone ringing ]
nice work, detective.

20:44.877 --> 20:46.677
You can't beat
a murder confession.

20:48.081 --> 20:50.348
If only it were true.

20:52.085 --> 20:54.585
Henry,
he said he did it.

20:54.587 --> 20:58.422
The murder weapon entered
sarah's neck from beneath,

20:58.424 --> 21:00.258
Yet based on
neville's pantomime,

21:00.260 --> 21:02.426
The angle of entry
was downward.

21:02.428 --> 21:05.930
We have the man who
owned the apartment in '79,

21:05.932 --> 21:08.532
Who created
some whack-a-doodle fantasy

21:08.534 --> 21:10.935
And then dumped a young co-ed
down a garbage chute.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.770
Listen, if --

21:12.772 --> 21:15.439
If you're looking for an excuse
to spend more time with molly,

21:15.441 --> 21:17.942
All you got to do
is ask her out.

21:17.944 --> 21:21.045
How long has it been
since you and abigail split up?

21:22.949 --> 21:25.283
It's been a while.

21:25.285 --> 21:29.387
Well, maybe it's time you
get yourself back out there.

21:29.389 --> 21:33.791
We have a closed case,
and you have a new scarf.

21:33.793 --> 21:35.826
What's the worst
that can happen, huh?

21:40.967 --> 21:45.069
[ crying ] oh, i told you
this was a terrible idea!

21:46.472 --> 21:48.506
The hostess thought
you were so sweet

21:48.508 --> 21:50.341
To take your mother
out to dinner.

21:50.343 --> 21:52.610
And did you see the way
everyone looked at us

21:52.612 --> 21:53.944
When you took my hand?

21:53.946 --> 21:55.279
No one was looking.

21:55.281 --> 21:57.448
Henry, you really are blind,
aren't you?

21:57.450 --> 21:58.816
Yes.

21:58.818 --> 22:00.918
Since the moment
i first saw you.

22:00.920 --> 22:03.321
Henry, look at us.

22:03.323 --> 22:04.755
We're ridiculous.

22:04.757 --> 22:06.957
A ridiculous love story.

22:06.959 --> 22:08.826
That what
makes us so special.

22:08.828 --> 22:10.995
Look, i want
to believe you,

22:10.997 --> 22:13.164
But every time
i look at you --

22:13.166 --> 22:14.165
Then don't.

22:14.167 --> 22:16.667
Close your eyes.

22:16.669 --> 22:18.636
[ sighs ]

22:18.638 --> 22:20.971
And where
do you imagine us?

22:20.973 --> 22:23.140
[ sighs ]

22:23.142 --> 22:26.043
[ "moonlight serenade" plays ]
the queensbury all-service club
in london.

22:26.045 --> 22:29.714
You're dressed
in your smart tuxedo.

22:29.716 --> 22:32.316
Glenn miller is playing.

22:32.318 --> 22:35.586
Then that's
where we are tonight.

22:41.394 --> 22:43.761
Molly: You're thinking
about the case, aren't you?

22:45.031 --> 22:47.798
The case, yes.
Sorry.

22:47.800 --> 22:49.066
No, no, it's okay.

22:49.068 --> 22:50.901
I can't stop thinking
about sarah, either.

22:50.903 --> 22:53.804
Detective martinez, my partner,
made me promise

22:53.806 --> 22:56.540
That i wouldn't talk about
any murders on our date.

22:56.542 --> 22:58.476
Oh, is that
what this is?

22:58.478 --> 22:59.977
Yes.

22:59.979 --> 23:01.345
Uh-huh.

23:01.347 --> 23:03.247
I'm not up on all
of the latest rituals...

23:03.249 --> 23:05.750
[ chuckles ]
...But be aware,
you're currently being courted.

23:05.752 --> 23:07.585
Duly noted.

23:07.587 --> 23:10.688
Here's to fate
bringing us back together

23:10.690 --> 23:12.823
And justice served.

23:16.829 --> 23:18.996
I'm not quite sure
that's the case.

23:18.998 --> 23:20.498
What do you mean?
I thought you had a confession.

23:20.500 --> 23:22.566
We do, but...

23:22.568 --> 23:23.934
Henry, stop.

23:23.936 --> 23:25.569
[ chuckling ] you can
talk murder on our date.

23:25.571 --> 23:27.605
It's fine.
[ chuckles ]

23:29.108 --> 23:32.410
There's something off about
his recollection of events.

23:32.412 --> 23:36.080
Is it possible that he had
a psychological break

23:36.082 --> 23:38.282
That would have prevented him
from remembering

23:38.284 --> 23:40.284
The manner in which
he stabbed her

23:40.286 --> 23:42.920
And then held her down
while she bled to death?
I'm sorry. Stop, stop.

23:42.922 --> 23:46.457
You're saying that neville held
her down and watched her die?

23:46.459 --> 23:49.794
Yes. I suppose that was part
of his perverse fantasy.

23:49.796 --> 23:52.730
No, that doesn't make any sense,
not based on his profile.

23:52.732 --> 23:55.266
I mean, his fantasy
was all about preservation.

23:55.268 --> 23:58.269
He was immortalizing
his late wife through sarah.

23:58.271 --> 24:01.939
Would you like
my expert opinion?

24:01.941 --> 24:03.607
Please, doctor.

24:03.609 --> 24:07.645
The only way you can really
understand someone's fantasy...

24:07.647 --> 24:08.979
Is to inhabit it.

24:08.981 --> 24:11.549
Now, that
sounds like a date.

24:17.824 --> 24:20.391
Well, i'm no stranger
to obsessive personalities,

24:20.393 --> 24:21.659
But this seems...

24:21.661 --> 24:24.094
Just like
stepping into the past.

24:24.096 --> 24:26.130
All right, you go outside
and come back in again.

24:26.132 --> 24:29.500
Remember, this time,
you are neville.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.807
Hi, honey.
I'm home.

24:36.809 --> 24:40.277
Did you come home
from a long day at the office?

24:40.279 --> 24:41.779
You hang up your coat,

24:41.781 --> 24:44.114
You tell me how wonderful
my cooking smells.

24:44.116 --> 24:46.684
Is that the smell
of molten cheese

24:46.686 --> 24:48.953
Bubbling over
a chemical flame?

24:48.955 --> 24:50.254
Mmm!

24:50.256 --> 24:53.324
Fondue -- my favorite!
Mm-hmm.

24:54.494 --> 24:56.026
What?
No kiss?

24:56.028 --> 24:58.095
Sorry.

25:00.633 --> 25:03.000
You, sir,
go enjoy your cocktail

25:03.002 --> 25:05.336
And let your little lady slip
into something more comfortable.

25:05.338 --> 25:08.305
It's at this point
i think that she would disrobe,

25:08.307 --> 25:10.774
Although i am not wearing
any lingerie.

25:13.613 --> 25:15.813
Well, i have
a very vivid imagination.

25:15.815 --> 25:17.681
I'm sure you do,
doctor.

25:21.187 --> 25:25.956
He sat here.
Notice the indentation.

25:25.958 --> 25:28.826
All right, well,
then where do i sit?

25:28.828 --> 25:30.394
There's only one
indentation.

25:30.396 --> 25:34.965
Well, i believe
<i>i'm</i> your seat.

25:34.967 --> 25:36.700
Well, we must be
precise.

25:36.702 --> 25:38.202
Mm-hmm.

25:49.515 --> 25:50.748
My glass.

25:50.750 --> 25:52.449
Forget it.

25:57.657 --> 25:59.757
A stain.

25:59.759 --> 26:01.992
Perhaps neville spilled his
drink the night of the murder.

26:01.994 --> 26:04.662
Okay, so he's clumsy.

26:04.664 --> 26:06.397
[ sighs ]

26:06.399 --> 26:08.499
No, no, no.
He's precise.
[ sighs ]

26:08.501 --> 26:10.501
Exacting.

26:10.503 --> 26:12.770
He's meticulous
about cleaning.

26:12.772 --> 26:15.105
Why on earth
would he have left this stain?

26:15.107 --> 26:17.675
Well, perhaps he didn't
remember spilling it.

26:20.046 --> 26:21.612
[ sighs ]

26:21.614 --> 26:23.747
Or perhaps there was
another ingredient

26:23.749 --> 26:25.816
In his evening cocktail.

26:27.253 --> 26:29.520
Drinks and a trip
to the morgue?

26:29.522 --> 26:32.022
This is the best date
i've had in years.

26:34.627 --> 26:37.461
I knew i recognized the odor --
ketamine.

26:37.463 --> 26:40.097
It smells like
dish detergent.

26:40.099 --> 26:42.366
Neville said he was drinking
from a soapy glass,

26:42.368 --> 26:45.269
When, in fact,
he was drugged.

26:45.271 --> 26:47.438
Well, by whom?

26:47.440 --> 26:50.774
Oh, someone who wanted
to destroy his fantasy,

26:50.776 --> 26:52.643
Not only
frame him for murder,

26:52.645 --> 26:55.112
But make him believe
he was responsible.

26:55.114 --> 27:00.050
You had me with the new scarf,
but i must admit...

27:00.052 --> 27:02.353
I am genuinely impressed.

27:03.322 --> 27:05.923
Well, i...
Do have my moments.

27:05.925 --> 27:08.826
Mm-hmm.
And right now's one of 'em.

27:19.171 --> 27:20.638
Whoo-hoo.
My day to sleep in,

27:20.640 --> 27:22.072
And i get a call
with him raving about neville.

27:22.074 --> 27:24.808
You know, i don't get it.
Didn't he confess?

27:24.810 --> 27:26.176
However, in re-enacting

27:26.178 --> 27:27.945
Neville's fantasy
in the apartment,

27:27.947 --> 27:29.346
We discovered a clue

27:29.348 --> 27:31.448
That will shed new light
on his confession.

27:31.450 --> 27:33.283
We? As in...

27:33.285 --> 27:36.620
Professor dawes accompanied me.
She was very helpful.

27:36.622 --> 27:39.256
You took molly
to the crime scene?

27:39.258 --> 27:41.291
Well, you're the one who
suggested i ask her on a date.

27:41.293 --> 27:43.360
Most people start
with dinner and a movie, doc.

27:43.362 --> 27:44.995
Lucas: Nope, not me --
too predictable.

27:44.997 --> 27:47.197
No, fear is
an underrated aphrodisiac.

27:47.199 --> 27:50.267
So, did the strategy pay...
Dividends?

27:52.605 --> 27:54.471
Afterwards...

27:54.473 --> 27:57.007
I brought her back to the lab,
and we ran a tox report

27:57.009 --> 27:58.876
Which proves that neville
was poisoned.

27:58.878 --> 28:01.679
Smooth! I bet that
buttered her muffin.

28:01.681 --> 28:03.113
Can someone
please tell me

28:03.115 --> 28:04.982
Why i got called in
from my tennis match

28:04.984 --> 28:07.284
To work a<i> closed</i> case?

28:07.286 --> 28:09.319
Uh, we...
Have made some new discoveries.

28:09.321 --> 28:10.821
Yeah.

28:10.823 --> 28:12.623
Doc thinks someone
slipped our murderer a mickey.

28:12.625 --> 28:14.525
Henry:
Ketamine, to be precise,

28:14.527 --> 28:16.660
In the neighborhood
of 250 milligrams,

28:16.662 --> 28:19.730
And when neville came to
with sarah's body before him

28:19.732 --> 28:21.532
And a fondue skewer
in his hand,

28:21.534 --> 28:24.702
His mind leapt to the grim,
logical conclusion.

28:24.704 --> 28:26.737
Lucas:
That he killed her?

28:26.739 --> 28:28.806
While someone else
snuck in

28:28.808 --> 28:31.008
While neville
was knocked out.

28:31.010 --> 28:32.509
And killed
his fake wife.

28:32.511 --> 28:34.545
Yeah, right, and left
the murder weapon in his hand.

28:34.547 --> 28:37.181
I don't know.
This sounds...
I agree.
It sounds farfetched.

28:37.183 --> 28:39.216
Well, it couldn't hurt
to talk to neville again.

28:41.387 --> 28:44.988
[ sighs ]
there goes my afternoon match.

28:44.990 --> 28:48.392
Mr. Neville,
do you take any medications --

28:48.394 --> 28:50.094
Sleeping pills,
tranquilizers?

28:50.096 --> 28:53.163
Any...
Recreational drugs?

28:53.165 --> 28:55.899
<i>Did you have anything to drink</i>
<i>the night of the murder?</i>

28:55.901 --> 28:58.535
[ sighs ]
my usual manhattan.

28:58.537 --> 28:59.770
Why?

28:59.772 --> 29:02.539
We recovered spilt bourbon
at the scene.

29:02.541 --> 29:04.174
It was laced
with a sedative.

29:04.944 --> 29:06.610
What sedative?

29:06.612 --> 29:08.846
Ketamine. It's an anesthetic,
but it can also be used --

29:08.848 --> 29:11.081
Recreationally.

29:12.351 --> 29:14.685
I know
what ketamine is.

29:14.687 --> 29:17.588
Did you catch that?
He...

29:19.358 --> 29:21.759
Of course you did.

29:21.761 --> 29:24.094
Would you be willing to subject
yourself to a blood test?

29:24.096 --> 29:26.463
Jo:
We may be able to prove

29:26.465 --> 29:28.665
That someone slipped ketamine
into your drink.

29:29.869 --> 29:33.537
But i already told you --
i did it.

29:34.940 --> 29:36.807
I killed sarah.

29:36.809 --> 29:39.443
<i>Mr. Neville, i'm not sure</i>
<i>you understand what i'm saying.</i>

29:39.445 --> 29:41.278
He knows what he's doing.

29:41.280 --> 29:43.147
He's covering for someone.

29:43.149 --> 29:46.383
Someone who framed him for
murder, destroyed his fantasy?

29:46.385 --> 29:48.919
Who could he possibly
be covering for?

29:48.921 --> 29:52.556
Another person whose life
was ruined when his wife died.

29:52.558 --> 29:54.892
Remember
neville's fantasy?

29:55.895 --> 29:59.797
The night when his wife told him
that she was pregnant.

29:59.799 --> 30:03.433
Cecily neville,
born november 20, 1979.

30:03.435 --> 30:06.003
Nine months after the night
neville wanted to immortalize.

30:06.005 --> 30:08.305
No wonder he wanted to go
back in time. Check it out.

30:08.307 --> 30:12.476
Daughter ran away from home
at 15, petty larceny charge.

30:12.478 --> 30:15.212
Two years ago,
she was arrested for possession.

30:16.248 --> 30:17.948
Ketamine.

30:17.950 --> 30:19.783
No wonder neville
took the blame.

30:19.785 --> 30:21.318
He was protecting
his daughter.

30:21.320 --> 30:22.319
Where is she now?

30:22.321 --> 30:23.921
Paroled last month.

30:23.923 --> 30:26.156
P.O.'s got her working
at a coffeehouse on 10th.

30:26.158 --> 30:28.525
Jo: Three days ago,

30:28.527 --> 30:31.929
A woman was murdered in an
apartment you used to live in.

30:31.931 --> 30:33.197
Okay.

30:34.667 --> 30:36.600
Sorry,
that's terrible.

30:36.602 --> 30:37.968
The same night,

30:37.970 --> 30:41.505
Your father was drugged
in the same apartment.

30:41.507 --> 30:42.940
This is getting weird.

30:42.942 --> 30:44.808
Cecily,
we'd like you to tell us

30:44.810 --> 30:47.211
About your relationship
with your father.

30:48.347 --> 30:49.513
There is none.

30:49.515 --> 30:51.849
Why?
Did something happen?

30:51.851 --> 30:53.450
My father
wasn't a bad person.

30:53.452 --> 30:54.685
It was like...

30:54.687 --> 30:56.286
He wasn't ever there,

30:56.288 --> 30:58.555
Not after my mom died.

30:58.557 --> 31:00.490
I knew
he didn't want me.

31:00.492 --> 31:04.127
I just reminded him of her --
mom -- so i left.

31:04.129 --> 31:06.029
You must have hated him.

31:06.031 --> 31:08.465
Too bad i was here
from noon to midnight,

31:08.467 --> 31:12.236
So check with my boss if you
think i killed his girlfriend.

31:12.238 --> 31:14.338
Detective martinez
said "woman,"

31:14.340 --> 31:17.474
But yet you knew
he was sleeping with her.

31:21.380 --> 31:24.648
The only photo
i have of my mom.

31:24.650 --> 31:27.050
Doesn't even seem like
she was real until...

31:27.052 --> 31:29.086
One day,

31:29.088 --> 31:34.157
A woman walks past the window
looking exactly like her --

31:34.159 --> 31:36.093
Same jacket.

31:36.095 --> 31:37.694
It was eerie.

31:37.696 --> 31:39.263
So i followed her,

31:39.265 --> 31:41.999
And she walked into the building
we used to live in.

31:45.237 --> 31:47.404
Of course, it wasn't her,

31:47.406 --> 31:50.107
Just some girl my dad had
dressed up to look like my mom

31:50.109 --> 31:51.341
So he could bang her.

31:51.343 --> 31:53.243
Jo: Is this the woman
you saw?

31:53.245 --> 31:55.178
No.

31:55.180 --> 31:56.513
Sorry.

31:57.917 --> 32:01.585
A healthy fantasy
returns us to reality.

32:01.587 --> 32:04.621
We can also lose ourselves
in fantasy

32:04.623 --> 32:06.056
And behave in ways

32:06.058 --> 32:08.425
That our rational selves
could never imagine.

32:08.427 --> 32:10.627
I'll see you all next time.

32:14.733 --> 32:16.767
Jennifer:
Professor dawes?

32:16.769 --> 32:19.269
I've been thinking
about switching majors,

32:19.271 --> 32:21.104
And i was wondering
if i could pick your brain?

32:21.106 --> 32:23.106
Sure. Why don't we talk
in my office?

32:29.481 --> 32:31.048
Neville said no one knew about
their secret '70s love nest.

32:31.050 --> 32:32.649
Yeah, yet cecily

32:32.651 --> 32:34.618
Followed a woman dressed
as her dead mother there.

32:34.620 --> 32:36.954
But if sarah wasn't our
mystery woman, who was she --

32:36.956 --> 32:38.221
Our killer?

32:38.223 --> 32:39.790
I've got it.

32:39.792 --> 32:42.793
What if someone was
impersonating the impersonator?

32:42.795 --> 32:44.461
Okay, that
just hurts my head.

32:44.463 --> 32:46.563
Sarah was dressed
as neville's dead wife.

32:46.565 --> 32:48.231
Because he was obsessed
with her,

32:48.233 --> 32:50.667
So who was obsessed
with sarah?

32:50.669 --> 32:52.269
Who dressed up as her?

32:52.271 --> 32:54.504
Who else
had access to her clothes?

32:54.506 --> 32:56.807
Her roommate.

32:56.809 --> 33:00.310
Molly: So, you want
to be a psych major?

33:00.312 --> 33:01.645
Maybe.

33:01.647 --> 33:03.647
I don't know.

33:03.649 --> 33:05.849
I'm trying
different things out.

33:05.851 --> 33:08.819
Isn't that what college
is all about -- experience?

33:08.821 --> 33:10.988
Well, education
is what it's about.

33:10.990 --> 33:12.022
Right.

33:12.024 --> 33:13.657
Of course.

33:13.659 --> 33:17.494
I just thought maybe
i could get outside myself.

33:17.496 --> 33:20.364
You made such a huge impact
in my friend's life,

33:20.366 --> 33:21.965
Someone i really
looked up to.

33:21.967 --> 33:23.000
Your friend?

33:23.002 --> 33:24.735
Sarah clancy?

33:25.838 --> 33:28.372
You're wearing
her coat.

33:28.374 --> 33:31.274
It makes me feel closer to her
when i wear it.

33:31.276 --> 33:32.376
[ chuckles ]

33:33.879 --> 33:35.946
Like she's still here.

33:38.684 --> 33:40.717
Jennifer,
i am so sorry, honey,

33:40.719 --> 33:42.519
But i'm late
for my next appointment,

33:42.521 --> 33:44.121
So let's
talk later, okay?

33:45.290 --> 33:47.391
Oh. Sure.

33:47.393 --> 33:48.725
Well,
thanks for chatting.

33:48.727 --> 33:50.427
Mm-hmm.

33:53.032 --> 33:54.865
[ exhales sharply ]

33:54.867 --> 33:56.433
[ door closes ]

34:01.874 --> 34:03.707
Woman: N.Y.P.D.

34:03.709 --> 34:05.809
N.Y.P.D., uh, i need to speak
with dr. Henry morgan, please.

34:05.811 --> 34:06.910
It's an emergency.

34:06.912 --> 34:08.378
One moment.

34:08.380 --> 34:09.880
[ telephone rings ]

34:09.882 --> 34:11.982
M.E.'s office.
This is lucas.

34:12.651 --> 34:13.550
[ grunts ]

34:14.386 --> 34:15.485
Hello?

34:16.555 --> 34:18.622
Yello?

34:21.193 --> 34:24.027
Hello?

34:24.029 --> 34:25.228
Jennifer?

34:25.230 --> 34:26.496
[ door closes ]

34:28.700 --> 34:30.901
We've been thinking
about the case wrong.

34:30.903 --> 34:34.004
[ cellphone ringing ]
it's always been about obsession
but the wrong person's.

34:36.075 --> 34:37.174
Hey.

34:39.111 --> 34:40.444
Lucas.

34:45.017 --> 34:48.251
Okay,
i will tell him.

34:48.253 --> 34:49.786
That was lucas.

34:49.788 --> 34:52.089
He said
you got a crank call.

34:52.091 --> 34:53.590
Uh, caller i.D.

34:53.592 --> 34:56.026
Said it was coming from
the n.Y.U. Psych department.

34:56.028 --> 34:58.261
What's wrong?

34:58.263 --> 35:02.933
Jennifer printed sarah's
class schedule for today.

35:02.935 --> 35:07.537
Sarah had dropped out
of all her classes except one.

35:08.941 --> 35:10.107
Molly's.

35:12.611 --> 35:14.878
[ molly whimpers ]
what did i do?

35:14.880 --> 35:17.114
Why did you
try and call the police?

35:17.116 --> 35:19.783
I really messed up.

35:19.785 --> 35:21.952
I just wanted
to rescue her,

35:21.954 --> 35:24.421
To get her away
from that disgusting old man!

35:24.423 --> 35:26.923
[ whimpers ]
you killed sarah?

35:26.925 --> 35:28.592
I didn't mean to!

35:28.594 --> 35:30.060
I was trying
to save her

35:30.062 --> 35:31.795
So that things could
go back to the way they were,

35:31.797 --> 35:35.298
But she got so mad,
and now...

35:35.300 --> 35:37.267
What do i do?!

35:37.269 --> 35:39.136
We tell the truth. I mean,
we'll -- we'll do it together.

35:39.138 --> 35:40.670
I know the police.

35:40.672 --> 35:43.073
I can just tell them
you had a psychotic break.

35:43.075 --> 35:45.342
Look, i'm not
some sort of psycho!

35:45.344 --> 35:46.943
No, i'm not saying
that you are.

35:46.945 --> 35:48.678
I'm not, honey.
That's an excuse.

35:48.680 --> 35:52.015
That's -- that's, um [sniffles]
it's a defense, okay?

35:52.017 --> 35:53.483
We all make mistakes.

35:53.485 --> 35:55.752
We -- we get caught up
in our fantasies.

35:55.754 --> 35:57.287
But what's important

35:57.289 --> 35:59.956
Is that we have to
come back down to reality, okay?

35:59.958 --> 36:03.160
No matter what the consequences,
we have to.

36:03.162 --> 36:05.395
[ door opens ]
henry: Molly!

36:07.166 --> 36:08.965
Molly, are you there?
[ muffled scream ]

36:08.967 --> 36:09.966
Professor?
Detective martinez.
[ pounding on door ]

36:09.968 --> 36:11.468
[ muffled scream ]

36:11.470 --> 36:12.269
Molly?

36:13.272 --> 36:14.838
[ muffled screaming ]

36:14.840 --> 36:16.273
Be quiet.

36:16.275 --> 36:17.407
Shh!

36:20.512 --> 36:21.678
[ muffled screaming ]
be quiet!

36:23.182 --> 36:25.482
Drop it! Put it down now!
Put it down!
[ gun cocks ]

36:25.484 --> 36:26.283
[ screams ]

36:26.285 --> 36:27.984
Call an ambulance.

36:27.986 --> 36:29.152
Molly!

36:29.154 --> 36:30.287
Back
against the wall!

36:30.289 --> 36:31.988
Oh, god.
[ breathing heavily ]

36:31.990 --> 36:34.324
Turn around!
Hands behind your back!

36:34.326 --> 36:37.494
This is detective jo martinez.
We need an ambulance.

36:37.496 --> 36:38.995
[ police radio chatter ]

36:38.997 --> 36:40.363
[ breathing shallowly ]

36:40.365 --> 36:42.199
[ weakly ]
m-my h-- my hero.

36:42.201 --> 36:44.701
[ sighs ]

36:49.007 --> 36:50.407
Woman over p.A.:<i> Dr. Shapiro</i>
<i>to the nurses' station.</i>

36:50.409 --> 36:52.242
<i>Dr. Shapiro</i>
<i>to the nurses' station.</i>

36:54.713 --> 36:57.581
I forgot
what this feels like.

36:57.583 --> 36:59.382
What's that?

36:59.384 --> 37:02.485
[ sighs ]
being scared...

37:02.487 --> 37:04.721
Vulnerable.

37:04.723 --> 37:08.191
Well, that's what happens
when you open yourself up.

37:08.193 --> 37:10.894
Yeah, i suppose.

37:10.896 --> 37:12.896
It's a good thing,
henry.

37:12.898 --> 37:14.531
I'm sure molly's
gonna be just --

37:14.533 --> 37:15.999
Doctor: Dr. Morgan?

37:16.001 --> 37:17.400
Patient's out of surgery.

37:17.402 --> 37:19.402
She lost a lot of blood,
but she's gonna be okay.

37:19.404 --> 37:20.570
[ sighs ]

37:20.572 --> 37:21.871
Can i see her?

37:21.873 --> 37:23.840
Uh, it's best
that she rests.

37:23.842 --> 37:25.909
[ elevator bell dings ]
um, n.Y.P.D.

37:25.911 --> 37:28.011
Mm, let him in.

37:35.887 --> 37:37.787
[ monitor beeping ]

37:38.890 --> 37:41.524
[ weakly ]
hello, henry.

37:43.962 --> 37:46.930
You want to know
a secret?

37:46.932 --> 37:51.901
I've always harbored
a "damsel in distress" fantasy.

37:51.903 --> 37:55.639
Being saved
by a dashing doctor was...

37:55.641 --> 37:59.309
It was kind of hot.

37:59.311 --> 38:01.478
[ sighs ]
i won't tell anyone.
Mm-hmm.

38:01.480 --> 38:03.146
Wouldn't want
to ruin your credibility

38:03.148 --> 38:04.547
With the dominatrix
community.

38:04.549 --> 38:06.983
Thank you.

38:06.985 --> 38:10.253
But i'm the one
that got my throat slashed,

38:10.255 --> 38:12.956
But, honey, you look
[chuckles] terrible.

38:12.958 --> 38:15.258
Well, thank you.

38:15.260 --> 38:16.726
It's been
a harrowing evening,

38:16.728 --> 38:18.295
Sitting out there,
worried about you.

38:18.297 --> 38:19.529
Mm.

38:34.413 --> 38:36.413
I don't know
how to say this...

38:38.150 --> 38:40.250
...But i've started to...

38:40.252 --> 38:42.986
Develop real feelings
for you, molly dawes.

38:44.623 --> 38:46.256
Isn't that
a good thing?

38:46.258 --> 38:49.159
Yes, usually.

38:51.196 --> 38:53.463
You're not a usual man,
though, huh?

38:53.465 --> 38:57.701
And you avoid real feelings
at all costs.

38:57.703 --> 39:00.770
Yes.

39:02.441 --> 39:05.408
Whoever she is,
she hurt you pretty bad, huh?

39:07.679 --> 39:09.846
Let's just say the...

39:09.848 --> 39:11.514
Wounds
haven't healed yet.

39:13.852 --> 39:15.852
I understand.

39:15.854 --> 39:18.355
But do me a favor,
henry --

39:18.357 --> 39:22.625
You ever decide you don't like
me so much, you call me, okay?

39:28.633 --> 39:30.300
[ sighs ]

39:34.840 --> 39:36.706
Reece: So, it was
the roommate, huh?

39:36.708 --> 39:38.742
Jo: She developed
an unhealthy obsession

39:38.744 --> 39:40.343
With our victim,
sarah clancy,

39:40.345 --> 39:42.245
And when she lost her
to someone else's fantasy,

39:42.247 --> 39:43.580
She snapped.

39:43.582 --> 39:44.881
Girl's a complete
whack job.

39:44.883 --> 39:47.050
That's the technical term,
boss.

39:47.052 --> 39:49.819
Don't joke. She's probably gonna
try to get off on a psych plea.
[ chuckles ]

39:49.821 --> 39:51.388
So, how's
professor dawes doing?

39:52.357 --> 39:53.990
Molly's recovering well.

39:53.992 --> 39:55.925
That's good. I'd like see
her and henry get together.

39:55.927 --> 39:57.394
[ elevator bell dings ]

39:57.396 --> 39:59.829
I know everything
that goes on in my precinct.

39:59.831 --> 40:02.532
[ "nothing will ever change
(this love of mine)" plays ]

40:02.534 --> 40:03.900
Henry: Abraham?

40:03.902 --> 40:05.902
Is that...

40:05.904 --> 40:07.404
Mom's lasagna!

40:07.406 --> 40:08.905
With secret sauce.

40:08.907 --> 40:11.207
[ sighs ]
¶ i got the message, baby ¶

40:11.209 --> 40:13.076
I'm shocked.
So am i.

40:13.078 --> 40:15.178
¶ you said this to me ¶
it turns out
that despite

40:15.180 --> 40:17.414
My ever-youthful,
forward-thinking...

40:17.416 --> 40:19.349
¶ and right now
i wanna tell you ¶
...21st-century ways,

40:19.351 --> 40:21.217
When it came down to throwing
away mom's old recipes,

40:21.219 --> 40:23.286
I just couldn't do it!

40:23.288 --> 40:25.422
¶ just how i feel ¶
now, i held this old cookbook
in my hands,

40:25.424 --> 40:27.957
And all of a sudden...

40:27.959 --> 40:29.726
¶ don't want your money, baby ¶
...I remembered coming home
from school and that smell.

40:29.728 --> 40:30.927
[ chuckles ]

40:30.929 --> 40:32.462
Abigail's cooking.
[ chuckles ]

40:32.464 --> 40:34.798
My mouth
started watering right away.

40:34.800 --> 40:37.033
¶ but nothing
will ever change ¶
you know...
It turns out that, uh,

40:37.035 --> 40:39.269
A pinch of nostalgia
might not be such a bad thing.

40:39.271 --> 40:42.372
¶ this love of mine ¶

40:43.942 --> 40:46.776
Mmm, for a moment,
it felt like she was still here.

40:46.778 --> 40:49.112
I know
just how you feel, pops.

40:49.114 --> 40:51.748
Henry:<i> Some memories</i>
<i>are so powerful</i>

40:51.750 --> 40:54.150
<i>That they never fade...</i>

40:54.152 --> 40:57.220
[ sniffs ]

40:57.222 --> 40:59.322
[ sighs ]
smells great, mom.

40:59.324 --> 41:00.457
Thank you.

41:00.459 --> 41:02.459
It's positively
pavlovian.

41:02.461 --> 41:03.626
Every time i smell it,

41:03.628 --> 41:05.228
I experience
this overwhelming desire

41:05.230 --> 41:07.130
To dance
with a beautiful woman.
[ chuckles ]

41:07.132 --> 41:08.665
No.

41:08.667 --> 41:09.933
Yes.
No, henry.

41:09.935 --> 41:11.034
Yes.

41:12.671 --> 41:14.337
I'm a mess.

41:14.339 --> 41:15.839
[ "moonlight serenade" plays ]

41:15.841 --> 41:17.407
You're perfect.
[ sighs ]

41:18.643 --> 41:20.977
Everything is perfect.

41:23.315 --> 41:25.849
<i>...Memories which become</i>
<i>more powerful</i>

41:25.851 --> 41:27.717
<i>Every time</i>
<i>we remember them...</i>

41:29.020 --> 41:30.987
[ voice breaking ]
this can't last forever.

41:30.989 --> 41:32.956
Shh.

41:32.958 --> 41:34.858
Let's not
think about that.

41:39.331 --> 41:42.499
<i>...Thus making</i>
<i>our present lives</i>

41:42.501 --> 41:44.601
<i>Seem a little more faded.</i>

41:46.171 --> 41:48.838
<i>But let's not</i>
<i>think about that now.</i>

41:48.840 --> 41:51.908
[ music continues ]
